# GitHub Sponsors / Funding Configuration Example

# FUNDING.yml
# 
# This file enables the "Sponsor" button on your GitHub profile and repositories.
# Place this file at: .github/FUNDING.yml
#
# Uncomment and add your accounts for the platforms you use:

# GitHub Sponsors
# github: [DenWin]  # Replace with your GitHub username

# Open Collective
# open_collective: your-collective-name

# Ko-fi
# ko_fi: your-kofi-name

# Tidelift
# tidelift: npm/package-name

# Community Bridge
# community_bridge: project-name

# Liberapay
# liberapay: your-liberapay-username

# IssueHunt
# issuehunt: your-issuehunt-username

# Otechie
# otechie: your-otechie-username

# LFX Mentorship (formerly CommunityBridge)
# lfx_crowdfunding: project-name

# Buy Me a Coffee
# custom: ['https://www.buymeacoffee.com/yourname']

# Patreon
# patreon: your-patreon-username

# Custom URLs (you can have multiple)
# custom: ['https://www.paypal.me/yourname', 'https://yourwebsite.com/donate']

---

## 📝 Usage Instructions

1. **Choose Your Platform(s)**
   - Decide which sponsorship platform(s) you want to use
   - You can enable multiple platforms simultaneously

2. **Set Up Your Account**
   - Create accounts on your chosen platform(s)
   - Configure your sponsorship tiers and goals

3. **Configure FUNDING.yml**
   - Copy this file to `.github/FUNDING.yml` in your repository
   - Uncomment the lines for your platform(s)
   - Replace placeholder values with your actual usernames/URLs

4. **Commit and Push**
   - The "Sponsor" button will appear on your profile within a few minutes

## 💡 Best Practices

- **Be Transparent**: Clearly state what sponsorships support (e.g., open source work, content creation)
- **Set Realistic Tiers**: Offer meaningful rewards at different sponsorship levels
- **Show Gratitude**: Acknowledge your sponsors in your projects
- **Update Regularly**: Keep your goals and tiers current

## 🎯 When to Use

Consider adding sponsorship options if you:
- Maintain popular open source projects
- Create technical content or tutorials
- Provide free tools or services to the community
- Want to dedicate more time to open source work

## ⚠️ Professional Context

Given your role at Avanade Deutschland GmbH:
- Ensure sponsorship doesn't conflict with employment agreements
- Consider whether sponsorship aligns with your professional brand
- Focus on knowledge sharing rather than financial gain
- Use it to support open source contributions, if applicable

---

**Example for Professional Developer Profile:**

```yaml
# github: DenWin
# custom: ['https://yourwebsite.com/contact']
```

This minimal setup shows you're open to sponsorship but keeps it professional.
